WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:16.000
upayātānāṃ sudṛśāṃ kusumāyudhabāṇapātavivaśānām |
abhivāñchitaṃ vidhātuṃ kṛtamatirapi tā jagātha vāmamiva ||1||
upayātānāṃ	who had come
sudṛśāṃ	the beautiful women
kusumāyudha-	(whom) Cupid's
bāṇa-pāta-	arrows strike
vivaśānām	(had made) helpless
abhivāñchitaṃ	desire
vidhātuṃ	to fulfil
kṛtamati:-api	having decided though
tā: jagātha	to them spoke
vāmam-iva	unfavourable like
Thou had decided to fulfil the desire of the beautiful women who had come to Thee. They were helpless as they were struck by Cupid's arrow for Thee. Yet Thou first spoke to them in an unfavourable manner.

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:31.000
gaganagataṃ muninivahaṃ śrāvayituṃ jagitha kulavadhūdharmam |
dharmyaṃ khalu te vacanaṃ karma tu no nirmalasya viśvāsyam ||2||
gagana-gataṃ	waiting in the skies
muni-nivahaṃ	the host of sages
śrāvayituṃ	to make them hear
jagitha	(Thou) stated
kula-vadhū-dharmam	the housewives' duties
dharmyam khalu	in accordance of Dharma indeed
te vacanaṃ	Thy words
karma tu no	actions but not
nirmalasya	of Thee who are pure
viśvāsyam	(are) to be followed
To the hearing of the sages assembled in the skies, Thou stated the duties of the housewives, for the benefit of the world. Indeed, Thy words are to be followed for they are in accordance with the Dharma. But the actions of Thee who are ever pure, should not be practiced by others, because Thy actions do not always conform to the good and bad standards of the world.

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:48.000
ākarṇya te pratīpāṃ vāṇīmeṇīdṛśa: paraṃ dīnā: |
mā mā karuṇāsindho parityajetyaticiraṃ vilepustā: ||3||
ākarṇya te	hearing Thy
pratīpāṃ vāṇīm-	unfavourable speech
eṇīdṛśa:	the doe eyed damsels
paraṃ dīnā:	very much grief stricken
mā mā	do not O do not
karuṇāsindho	O Thou ocean of compassion
parityaja-iti-	forsake thus
aciraṃ	for long
vilepu:-tā:	pleaded they
On hearing Thy unfavourable speech, those doe eyed women were very much grief stricken. For long did they plead saying 'O Thou ocean of compassion, do not, O do not forsake us.'

00:00:48.000 --> 00:01:03.000
tāsāṃ ruditairlapitai: karuṇākulamānaso murāre tvam |
tābhissamaṃ pravṛtto yamunāpulineṣu kāmamabhirantum ||4||
tāsāṃ ruditai:-	by their weeping
lapitai:	(and) pleading
karuṇā-ākula-	with pity moved
mānasa:	Thy mind
murāre tvam	O Slayer of Mur! Thou
tābhi:-samam	with them
pravṛtta:	set out
yamunā-pulineṣu	on the Yamunaa sand banks
kāmam-abhirantum	desiring to sport freely
O Thou! Slayer of Mura! Moved with pity by their weeping and pleading, Thou set out to sport freely with them on the sand banks of Yamunaa river.

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:20.000
candrakarasyandalasatsundarayamunātaṭāntavīthīṣu |
gopījanottarīyairāpāditasaṃstaro nyaṣīdastvam ||5||
candrakara-	the moon light
syanda-lasat-	flowing and shining
sundara-	beautifully
yamunā-taṭānta-	on the Yamunaa banks
vīthīṣu	and the sand banks
gopījana-	the Gopikaas
uttarīyai:-	(by their) upper garment
āpādita-saṃstara:	spread out bed
nyaṣīda:-tvam	sat down Thou
The sand banks of Yamunaa was lit by beautifully flowing and shining moon light. There Thou sat down on the bed which was made by the Gopikaas by spreading out their upper garment.

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:37.000
sumadhuranarmālapanai: karasaṃgrahaṇaiśca cumbanollāsai: |
